g.text: 1.) id are generated concurrently , so mutex with
lock and unlock are used to avoid race condn
2.) the least significant figure for time is 10ms.
and hence when when more than 1 id is generated
in 10 ms the sequence is increased.
3.) in case of sequence overflow the internal clock
is increased , and then the ids are generated .
4.) if the real time and internal time have
difference sleep or increment is done .
